  "name": "Dark Data Medicine: The Open Negative Results Registry",
  "description": "An open, structured, and freely accessible registry of negative and null results in medical and biomedical research. Reduces duplicated research effort caused by publication bias by giving negative findings -- including preclinical and early-phase results that fall outside formal clinical trial registries -- a permanent, citable, machine-readable home.",
